    </div></td><td width="32">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><div class="es-jasper-simpleCalendar" baseurl="/lkml/"></div><div class="threadlist">Messages in this thread</div><ul class="threadlist"><li class="root"><a href="/lkml/1997/7/27/2">First message in thread</a></li><li class="origin"><a href="">Linus Torvalds</a></li></ul></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerl.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="/" /></td><td class="c" rowspan="2" valign="top" style="padding-top: 1em"><table><tr><td colspan="2"><!--BuySellAds Zone Code--><div id="bsap_1305798" class="bsarocks bsap_5aa49c00cc06c882289a1dd6a5e50b62"></div><!--End BuySellAds Zone Code--></td></tr><tr><td><table><tr><td class="lp">Date</td><td class="rp" itemprop="datePublished">Sat, 26 Jul 1997 22:10:05 -0700 (PDT)</td></tr><tr><td class="lp">From</td><td class="rp" itemprop="author">Linus Torvalds &lt;&gt;</td></tr><tr><td class="lp">Subject</td><td class="rp" itemprop="name">Re: d_path to be removed?</td></tr></table></td><td><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></td></tr></table><pre itemprop="articleBody"><br /><br />On Sat, 26 Jul 1997 torvalds&#64;penguin.transmeta.com wrote:<br />&gt; <br />&gt; I suspect the code will look something like this:<br />&gt; <br />&gt; 	/*<br />&gt; 	 * "buflen" should be PAGE_SIZE or more.<br />&gt; 	 */<br />&gt; 	char * d_path(struct dentry *dentry, char *buffer, int buflen)<br />&gt; 	{<br />&gt; 		char * end = buffer+buflen;<br />&gt; 		char * retval;<br />&gt; 		struct dentry * root = current-&gt;fs-&gt;root;<br />&gt; <br />&gt; 		*--end = '\0';<br />&gt; 		buflen--;<br />&gt; <br />&gt; 		/* Get '/' right */<br />&gt; 		retval = end-1;<br />&gt; 		*retval = '/';<br />&gt; <br />&gt; 		for (;;) {<br />&gt; 			struct dentry * parent;<br />&gt; 			int namelen;<br />&gt; <br />&gt; 			parent = dentry-&gt;d_covers-&gt;d_parent;<br />&gt; 			if (dentry == root || dentry == parent)<br />&gt; 				break;<br />&gt; 			namelen = dentry-&gt;d_name.len;<br />&gt; 			buflen -= namelen + 1;<br />&gt; 			if (buflen &lt; 0)<br />&gt; 				break;<br />&gt; 			end -= namelen;<br />&gt; 			memcpy(end, dentry-&gt;d_name.name, namelen);<br />&gt; 			*--end = '/';<br />&gt; 			retval = end;<br />&gt; 		}<br />&gt; 		return retval;<br />&gt; 	}<br />&gt; <br />&gt; The above is what I currently have, but it's untested. Feel free to<br />&gt; test.<br /><br />I warned you.<br /><br />Anyway, the loop obviously needs a "dentry = parent;" at the end,<br />otherwise it will never move downwards in the directory tree.<br /><br />It still isn't tested, though.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
